==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-dot.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A small spot.
#:''a dot of colour''
#A symbol ( . ) having numerous uses, including, and not limited to:
##marking the end of a sentence (a [[full stop]] or [[period]]);
##replacing the part of a word or words removed to form an [[abbreviation]];
##in [[mathematics]], separating the [[decimal part]] of a [[decimal]] from the [[whole part]], indicating [[multiplication]], a [[scalar product]], or in various other meanings;
##as one of the symbols used in [[Morse code]].

====Synonyms====
*(''small spot''): [[speck]], [[spot]]
*(''symbol''):
**(''at the end of a sentence''): {{UK}} [[full stop]], {{UK}} [[period]]
**(''in an abbreviation''): [[point]]
**(''mathematics''): (''in a decimal'') [[decimal point]]
**(''in Morse code''): [[dit]]

